column5: Leaving Thursday bright and early coming back Sunday , hopefully injury free ... Aiming for a few Walleye shore lunches and my main goal is some pike in the 40+'s  Report to follow. .  Randy .
Have fun! Have fished it myself on a couple of occasions, nice lake.
cool. Looking forward to the write up. Enjoy!
Good stuff Randy. I'm sure you'll have a great time up there. Just don't break the camera so that we too can enjoy your trip.  Stay safe.

I am very interested in reading about your trip and any other trips you have had to this lake. I've been up that way a few times (Wakami, the Domtar rd through to Webbwood etc) and have looked at that lake on the map on more than a few occasions and thought it would be an ideal place to go.  Please share about this years trip and any other trips you've been on up there, very interested in reading about access point(s), fishing quality, campsites and anything else in general.  Thanks very much
good luck Randy, let us know how you do
